## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Purpose

PC Playground is designed to simplify the process of checking component compatibility while assembling your computer. It ensures that the selected components work seamlessly together.

### 1.2 Features

- User-friendly interface
- Component dropdown menus
- Real-time compatibility checks
- Error messages for troubleshooting

### 1.3 System Requirements

- Python 3.x
- Tkinter library

## 2. Getting Started

### 2.1 Installation

1. Clone the repository to your local machine:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/pc-playground.git
Navigate to the project directory:

   '''bash
    cd pc-playground

2.2 Launching the Application

   - Open a terminal in the project directory.

   - Run the application:

   - bash

   - python pc_playground.py

### 3. Using PC Playground
3.1 Component Selection

   - Open PC Playground and select components from the dropdown menus.

3.2 Checking Compatibility

   - Click the "Check Compatibility" button.
   - Review the compatibility result displayed on the screen.

### 4. Troubleshooting
4.1 Incomplete Component Selection

If the compatibility check fails due to incomplete component selection, ensure all components are chosen before checking.
4.2 Motherboard and CPU Socket Mismatch

If a mismatch error occurs, verify that the CPU and motherboard sockets match.
4.3 Insufficient Power Supply

If an insufficient power supply error occurs, check if the total power consumption exceeds the power supply wattage.
### 5. Closing the Application

Close the PC Playground application window when finished.
